<TITLE> 'War crime charge sheet by May' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 26 (bdnews24.com)  The war crimes investigative agency will submit charge sheets against a number of alleged criminals by May, law minister Shafique Ahmed said on Sunday. "The investigative agency has confirmed to us that it will submit the charge sheet against some of the war criminals accused of committing crimes against humanity in 1971," Shafique said this following an inter-ministerial meeting. . Initially, a few accused will be brought to justice. Gradually, others will also be charged, the minister said. "This was our first meeting with the investigative agency and the panel of lawyers. They were asked to strengthen coordination between them." Home minister Sahara Khatun told reporters, "No one will be able to escape from the hands of justice. Even those, who are fugitives, will be brought back." She said the government would provide the panel and the agency with all necessary logistic support. On Mar 25, the government, established a war crimes tribunal, investigative agency and a prosecution panel. A number of organisations, including the War Crimes Fact Finding Committee, Ain O Shalish Kendra, the Liberation War Museum and Bangla Academy, have given information to the investigative agency. bd
